The paper deals with image representations derived from pre-trained CNNs for computer vision tasks such as instance retrieval, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the suitability of Faster R-CNN features for instance retrieval, which involves information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves spatial reranking, which is a common technique in multimedia retrieval (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
